TY  - JOUR
T1  - Efficient Algorithms for Stochastic Dominance Tests Based on Financial Market Data
AU  - Aboudi, Ronny
AU  - Thon, Dominique
Y1  - 1994/04/01
PY  - 1994
DA  - 1994/04/01
N1  - doi: 10.1287/mnsc.40.4.508
DO  - 10.1287/mnsc.40.4.508
T2  - Management Science
JF  - Management Science
JO  - Management Science
SP  - 508
EP  - 515
VL  - 40
IS  - 4
PB  - INFORMS
N2  - It is known that when the random variables being compared have a uniform probability measure, as is the case when using financial market data, the computation of efficient sets for first- and second-degree dominance can be greatly simplified if majorization conditions are used instead of the dominance definitions. This paper presents an equally efficient technique for third-degree dominance.
